In order to deny the right to the root user to connect in shh follow the path : 

step 1 : you need to modify the file /etc/ssh/sshd_config (again)
step 2 : find the line PermitRootLogin 
step 3 : uncomment it 
step 4 : put no if there is a yes at the end of the line
step 5 : save it
step 6 : reboot the machine
step 7 : ???
step 8 : profit

